==English==
===Phrasal verb===
'''to [[tip]] one's [[hand]]'''
#In [[card]] [[play]]ing, to accidentally [[reveal]] one's cards or [[hand]].
#{{idiom}} To inadvertantly reveal any [[secret]], particularly a secret that puts one at an [[advantage]] or [[disadvantage]].
#:''Do not '''tip your hand''' during the negotiation, but keep your lowest acceptable price a secret.''
